{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01TxwoeVtJBC2DtxsCj8Y7JM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The head node was started with `ray start --head --node-ip-address=\"${MY_POD_IP}\" --port=6379 --include-dashboard=true --dashboard-host=0.0.0.0 --num-cpus=0 --block`.\n\nPort 6379 is the GCS port. The head node doesn't include `--ray-client-server-port` explicitly (defaults to 10001), but the service doesn't expose port 10001.\n\nSo `ray://ray-head:10001` won't work because the service doesn't expose port 10001.\n\nThe issue is that `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` in Ray 2.9.0 tries to join as a worker node (which requires `ray start` to have been run on the same host), not just connect as a client.\nLooking at the error logs, the connection to the GCS at ray-head:6379 is actually succeeding, but then it's trying to find a local session file, which is the behavior of starting a worker node rather than just connecting as a client.\n\nThe issue is that when the client pod calls `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")`, it connects to the head's GCS and retrieves the session directory path (which belongs to the head pod), but then tries to locate that same path locally on the client pod where it doesn't exist. The session timestamp `2026-06-16_02-26-35_897098_13` is from the head's session, not the client's, so the client can't find `/tmp/ray/session_2026-06-16_02-26-35_897098_13/node_ip_address.json` in its own filesystem.\n\nTo resolve this, I could either expose port 10001 on the ray-head service and use the Ray Client protocol (`ray://ray-head:10001`), or take a simpler approach where the job script just initializes Ray and prints \"pong\" without needing to access that session file. The issue is that `ray-head:6379` is the Redis port, not the Ray head service port. I need to figure out the right way to connect—either the Ray client pod needs to run `ray start` to join the cluster, or I should use a different connection method that works with the exposed ports.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1272,"cache_read_input_tokens":40853,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1272},"output_tokens":54,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1fbf2895-253f-4b32-a4d0-58f3f429940b","uuid":"23c0cf83-475d-4fc0-b0f3-2275dc48f8dc","request_id":"req_011Cc6iPMrEoMagbJ5ffo9SD"}
